The Herald Zvamaida MurwiraÂ Senior Reporter Outgoing Turkish Ambassador to Zimbabwe Hakan Kivanc today bade farewell to President Mnangagwa after a five-year tour of duty in the country. Briefing journalists soon after an hour-long discussion with President Mnangagwa at State House in Harare, Ambassador Kivanc said the bilateral relations between Zimbabwe and Turkey were encouraging. He said what remains was to enhance trade ties between Harare and Ankara which remained low.